<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-10T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">653.116/154: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-10T14:00:00+01:00">August 10, 1934—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 10—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Decree of August 7th effective in 15 days increases port dues in
                                port of Lisbon but exempts Portuguese vessels and those of countries
                                which have secured abolition of flag discrimination from 50 percent
                                of heavy stationing charge.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>